AmaZulu King Misuzulu kaZwelithini visits families affected by the KZN Floods. Courtesy #DStv403 DURBAN - The AmaZulu King, Misuzulu kaZwelithini, has visited families affected by the floods in Kwa Zulu-Natal. He says that in such times it helps to be united as a nation. The King was part of a delegation along with billionaire, Patrice Motsepe, who donates R30 million for relief. READ: KZN floods death toll increases to 398 He says everyone is shocked and affected. "It hurts as we speak at this point, there’s still people who have not been found, the number of missing people is so high and its shocking" The province's floods death toll has increased to 398. At least 264 schools across the province have been affected.   The AmaZulu King, Misuzulu kaZwelithini, has visited families affected by the floods in KwaZulu-Natal. He says that in such times it helps to be united as a nation. #KZNFlood #DStv403 #eNCA pic.twitter.com/6UgeKNHKZ5